news.title: Indore: Legal ownership of land set to be provided in 400 villages
news.para: In the remaining 321 villages, the administration is facing some technical issues or the same have been listed in the ‘abandoned’ category in the existing records.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Floor space index rate changed for properties along metro
news.para: All properties located 500m from central line of the metro rail corridor that is proposed, under construction or completed and for which administrative sanction has been accorded, the premium FSI will be charged 50% of the applicable premium FSI.

news.title: Over 80 structures in Pune rural not fit for habitation
news.para: With the Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) area spread across 7,000 sqkm, most of these structures are in rural areas and notices to evacuate them have been issued by the gram panchayats, said a senior PMRDA official.

news.title: Nagpur: Within a year, PMAY flats face rainwater seepage, cracks & various other problems
news.para: Under PMAY, NMRDA had constructed 942 flats on khasra no. 62 under mouza Tarodi. There are 48 wings with G+4 floors each. NMRDA had handed over possession of 450 flats, of which 320 are occupied.

news.title: Centre orders release of Rs 35.28 crore under PMAY-Gramin to Punjab
news.para: The directions came after Punjab Rural Development Minister Kuldeep Singh Dhaliwal brought to the knowledge of Patil the pending funds under the scheme, an official release issued here said.

news.title: Benami transactions laws cannot be applied retrospectively: SC
news.para: The top court said the continued presence of an unconstitutional law on the statute book does not prevent it from holding that such unconstitutional laws cannot enure to the benefit of or be utilised to retroactively amend laws to cure existing constitutional defects.

news.title: Ghaziabad: CMO seeks details of properties eligible for leasehold to freehold conversion
news.para: Before GDA took over in 2013, anyone willing to convert their leasehold properties to freehold would have to pay just 2% of the circle rate.

news.title: Infosys leases five lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: "The software major will be paying a rental of around ₹51 per sq ft. The lease term has a five-year lock-in period with a 15-year lease," said three people aware of the deal.

news.title: Noida authority files police complaint against Supertech over faulty STP in society
news.para: "The inspection conducted by a team of the Authority's Jal department found that Supertech Ecociti in Sector 137 has a functional STP but its treated water quality did not match the NGT standards," states the August 18 complaint issued by assistant manager of Noida Authority, H U Farooq.

news.title: Bankers are steadily loosening their purse strings for builders
news.para: Commercial banks net credit to the real estate sector witnessed 3.5 times growth during 2021, as compared to the pandemic period, shows the Reserve Bank of India's data on sectoral lending.

news.title: Shimao Group looks to repay $11.8 billion debt over 3-8 years: Sources
news.para: Shanghai-based Shimao, which first missed a public offshore bond obligation last month, is the first major Chinese developer to kick off negotiations on restructuring terms with creditors.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco earns Rs 298 crore from e-auction of four Nerul plots
news.para: ​​The sale of the fifth plot, with the biggest area of over 25,000sqm (over six acres), has been stayed by the National Green Tribunal (NGT) following protests by environmentalists as it partially falls within the CRZ.

news.title: I-T searches on premises of Phoenix group in Hyderabad
news.para: Chukkapalli Avinash and others run the group and are into top real estate projects in the city. I-T is looking into the suspected income tax evasion by the real estate firm.

news.title: Slum dwellers rush to Gujarat HC over Ahmedabad civic body's demolition bid
news.para: The AMC filed an application on July 7 and urged the HC for an early hearing on the petition filed by the slum dwellers, who have been demanding alternative accommodation if the civic body and government want to implement TP Scheme No. 5 (City Wall Improvement) Section-3.

news.title: Goa: SIT says real land owners not claiming properties
news.para: The SIT itself has registered 12 first information reports (FIRs) pertaining to land-grab, while 28 FIRs were transferred to it.
